,Recommended,220160,8614459,"Posted: 7 January, 2014",all,Sharp,"After playing the demo of this game for hours on end, I finally found a holiday sale price that suits my budget. This is probably the only game by Ubisoft that made me not slam my face into my keyboard. The game makes a pretty good first impression. You click play and some kickass rock n' roll music fills the main menu. After customizing your rider with a variety of colors, it's time to hit the track!The controls are very easy to master: arrows keys. That's it. The game feels like those old Flash games with the little biker trying to get to the other side of the screen. There are 2 campaigns to play, one consisting of a variety of motocross (and non-motocross events that don't even involve a bike) and the other campaign taking place in a warehouse full of explosions, and you're driving in the middle of it. The difficulty of this game creates a wonderful challenge for such a simple game!The game engine seems to work somewhat well, and the level editor even allows you to make more than tracks with motorcycles. For example, there is an entire campaign consisting of random minigames, one involoing making a metal ball roll down a pipe. There are glitches in the game like the bike floating on top of track instead of the wheels fully touching the ground and falling through tracks, but they are rather rare. The Steam connection breaks when you try to enter multiplayer, but quick matches work fine. Downloading the game also requires downloading Uplay (Ubisoft's version of Steam that is a pain).In conclusion, this addicting game is fun to play, but the normal price is way too high. The game seems to only be a good buy when I got it at the Holiday Sale.I'll give it an 8.5/10Stay tuned for more reviews!"
